    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Block the right countershaft assembly against the case wall and pull the mainshaft assembly to the rear to
            free the pilot from the input shaft pocket (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302162">left, Figure 62</hotlnk>). Tilt the front of the mainshaft up and lift the
            assembly from the case (right).
            <emph type="bold">Use caution as the reverse gear is free and can fall from the shaft.</emph>
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302162" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302162" filename="../figg13/G1302162.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 62. Mainshaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
